## ANIMATION RULES (Framer Motion)

### Page load — stagger everything
```tsx
const container = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0 },
  show: {
    opacity: 1,
    transition: { staggerChildren: 0.1, delayChildren: 0.2 }
  }
}
const item = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 24 },
  show:   { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.6, ease: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] } }
}
// Usage: <motion.div variants={container} initial="hidden" animate="show">
//          <motion.h1 variants={item}>...</motion.h1>
//        </motion.div>
```

### Scroll reveals — every section
```tsx
import { useInView } from 'framer-motion'
// Or use:
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 40 }}
  whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-80px" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.7, ease: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] }}
>
```

### Hover states — all cards/links
```tsx
<motion.div
  whileHover={{ y: -4, scale: 1.01 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.2, ease: "easeOut" }}
>
```

### Cursor glow effect (optional but premium)
Track mouse position with `useMotionValue`, render a blurred radial gradient that follows cursor.

### Text animations
- Hero name: split into chars, stagger animate with `y: 100 → 0` (clip with overflow-hidden)
- Section headers: slide in from left
- NEVER use typewriter effect — it's overdone

